<i>by the full</i>
<i>House of Representatives</i>
<i>now is a virtual certainty.</i>

65
00:03:28,722 --> 00:03:30,656
<i>These are,</i>
<i>with no serious doubt,</i>

66
00:03:30,724 --> 00:03:34,160
<i>the last hours</i>
<i>of the 37th presidency</i>
<i>of the United States.</i>

67
00:03:38,431 --> 00:03:40,626
<i>This is indeed</i>
<i>an historic day,</i>

68
00:03:40,700 --> 00:03:44,329
<i>the only time</i>
<i>a president has ever</i>
<i>resigned from office</i>

69
00:03:44,404 --> 00:03:47,066
<i>in our nearly 200</i>
<i>years of history.</i>

70
00:03:47,140 --> 00:03:50,041
<i>You see the White House</i>
<i>there, and in the White House,</i>

71
00:03:50,110 --> 00:03:51,441
<i>in just a few moments now,</i>

72
00:03:51,511 --> 00:03:54,605
<i>President Nixon</i>
<i>will be appearing</i>
<i>before the people,</i>

73
00:03:54,681 --> 00:03:58,583
<i>perhaps for the last</i>
<i>time as President</i>
<i>of the United States.</i>

74
00:03:59,953 --> 00:04:02,148
WHITE HOUSE DIRECTOR:
15 seconds, Mr. President.

75
00:04:08,028 --> 00:04:11,725
Okay, that's five,
four, three...

76
00:04:15,569 --> 00:04:18,697
Good evening.
This is the 37th time

77
00:04:18,772 --> 00:04:21,502
I have spoken to you
from this office

78
00:04:21,575 --> 00:04:24,135
where so many decisions
have been made

79
00:04:24,210 --> 00:04:26,735
that have shaped
the history of our nation.

80
00:04:26,813 --> 00:04:28,804
I remember exactly
where I was.

81
00:04:30,216 --> 00:04:33,583
My father called.
The phone rang, my father
called and he said,

82
00:04:33,653 --> 00:04:36,918
"Turn on the TV right now.
Richard Nixon's going down."

83
00:04:36,990 --> 00:04:40,721
I was at home with friends,
and we were watching
television at home.

84
00:04:40,794 --> 00:04:43,592
We stayed up and,
like everyone else,
I'd been glued to

85
00:04:43,663 --> 00:04:46,154
the Select and Judiciary
Committee hearings
night after night.

86
00:04:46,232 --> 00:04:48,359
And then finally,
it had come to this.

87
00:04:48,435 --> 00:04:54,237
Therefore, I shall resign
the presidency effective
at noon tomorrow.

88
00:04:54,307 --> 00:04:57,299
But instead of
the satisfaction
I imagined I'd feel,

89
00:04:57,377 --> 00:04:59,641
I just got angrier
and angrier,

90
00:04:59,713 --> 00:05:02,477
because there was
no admission of guilt.

91
00:05:02,549 --> 00:05:03,982
There was no apology.

92
00:05:04,050 --> 00:05:05,449
Little did I know

93
00:05:05,518 --> 00:05:07,645
that I would one day
be part of the team

94
00:05:07,721 --> 00:05:10,121
that would try and
elicit that apology.

95
00:05:10,190 --> 00:05:13,216
NIXON: To leave office
before my term is completed

96
00:05:13,293 --> 00:05:16,285
is abhorrent to every
instinct in my body.

97
00:05:16,363 --> 00:05:18,854
I have never been a quitter.

98
00:05:18,932 --> 00:05:20,593
And that that team
would be led

99
00:05:20,667 --> 00:05:24,364
by the most unlikely
of white knights,

100
00:05:24,437 --> 00:05:26,371
a man with no
political convictions
whatsoever,

101
00:05:26,439 --> 00:05:30,671
a man who, as far as I know,
had never even voted
once in his life.

102
00:05:31,478 --> 00:05:35,608
But he was a man who had
one big advantage
over the rest of us.

103
00:05:36,883 --> 00:05:39,181
He understood television.

104
00:05:39,719 --> 00:05:41,880
(FROST OVER AUSTRALIA
<i>THEME MUSIC PLAYING)</i>

